narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Professor Jordn did an amazing job covering a broad span of concepts pertaining to Early Modern Spanish histories. We had readings that encompassed both broader Spanish histories and micro-histories.

I really enjoyed how the course material did not follow a textbook, but was constructed of a mix of primary and secondary sources selected by Professor Jordan. This format yielded a very engaging way of approaching historical events.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: Professor Jordn! She makes the content interesting and discussions lively. No weaknesses!

This course was held in seminar style and was heavily centred around the discussion of the readings. For students in the class who werent history majors, it would have been more useful to perhaps have some more background information taught in class before launching straight into the discussion.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: YES! Please take this course, especially if offered by Professor Jordn. She fosters an inclusive, inviting classroom environment and encourages all students to participate and engage with the class content.
